author: tqrmt
content: it's hard to put into words just how deep this experience was, but i'll try. it wasn't just a moment-it was an epiphany, a soul-shaking realization that uprooted everything i thought i knew. i found myself submerged in a depth of emotion that i didn't even know was possible, and it truly changed my entire perspective on life. the way it struck me, it was as if every preconceived notion i had about the world and myself crumbled, replaced with a clarity that was both painful and beautiful at the same time. you don't expect something like that to happen until it does, and when it does, it feels like the ground beneath you shifts, leaving you weightless in the vastness of your thoughts and emotions. the tears weren't just flowing they poured from my eyes as if they had been bottled up for years, waiting for this moment to be set free. every drop carried weight of unspoken fears, unresolved conflicts, and, most of all, the deep-rooted realization of how small we are in the grand scheme of things, and yet how significant every choice, every action, every moment really is. it was like standing at the edge of the universe, staring into an endless abyss, only to realize that the abyss was staring back at me, reflecting everything i am and everything i'm not. the sheer intensity of it all, the overwhelming emotion, left me breathless, as if my soul was crying out in a way my body never could. and it wasn't just the tears-it was the release, the catharsis, the strange sense of peace that followed after what felt like an eternity of chaos within. it was as though the floodgates had opened, not just in my eyes but in my heart and mind too, letting everything out and leaving me in awe of how much i had been holding back without even realizing it. this moment, this shift, wasn't just about what i was feeling it was about who i had become and who i was destined to be from that point forward.
